President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on May 24, 2019, in honor of Memorial Day. He emphasized the importance of remembering and honoring the brave Americans who have sacrificed their lives in defense of the country and its founding ideals. President Trump called on the American people to ensure that the sacrifices made by these patriots were not in vain and to provide comfort and support to the families left behind. He also highlighted the upcoming 75th anniversary of D-Day and the sacrifices made by members of the Armed Forces on the beaches of Normandy. President Trump urged unity and prayer for lasting peace, while also designating specific times for prayer and remembrance on Memorial Day. He requested that the flag be flown at half-staff until noon and encouraged citizens to display the flag at half-staff from their homes. The proclamation serves as a reminder of the importance of honoring and remembering the sacrifices made by America's fallen heroes.